14 "§ 126A-23. Decentralization agreements.
15 (a) Decentralization agreements with executive branch agencies shall require a person
16 designated by the agency to be accountable to the Director for the compliance of all personnel
17 actions taken pursuant to the delegated authority of the agency. The agreement shall specify the
18 required policies for agency personnel administration.
19 (b) The Director shall take appropriate corrective actions, including adjusting employee
20 salaries and changing classifications that are not in compliance with policy, and suspend
21 decentralization agreements when agencies are not in compliance with personnel administration
22 policies.
23 "§ 126A-24. State of the State workforce report and survey.
24 (a) OSHR shall annually report by January 15 on the state of the State employee
25 workforce and statewide human resources programs to the Joint Legislative Commission on
26 Governmental Operations, the Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on General Government,
27 the Fiscal Research Division, and the Appropriations Committees of the House of
28 Representatives and the Senate. The report shall include the following:
29 (1) A comparison of employee compensation rates and benefits compared to
30 national trends, including at least the following:
31 a. An overview of economic conditions and labor market trends.
32 b. An analysis of the competitiveness of State salaries and benefits.
33 c. A review of recruitment and retention efforts and results.
34 d. The results of the annual compensation surveys conducted pursuant to
35 subsection (b) of this section.
36 (2) The safety, health, and workers' compensation activities of agencies in
37 compliance with Article 13 of this Chapter and the fines levied against
38 agencies pursuant to Article 16 of Chapter 95 of the General Statutes.
39 (3) The costs associated with the defense or settlement of administrative
40 grievances and lawsuits filed by current or former employees and applicants
41 for employment with an agency.
42 (4) Agency compliance with JoinNC policies, including the following:
43 a. The number and type of exceptions made by the Director.
44 b. A list of agencies with invoices more than 60 days overdue.
45 c. A list of agencies with temporary employees who exceeded 11 months
46 of consecutive employment, including the number of employees who
47 exceeded 11 months of consecutive employment and the average
48 number of days employees exceeded this limit.
49 (b) OSHR shall conduct annual compensation surveys to guide the Governor and the
50 General Assembly in making decisions regarding the compensation of employees.
51 "Article 3.
