12 "Article 11.
13 "Temporary Employees.
14 "§ 126A-110. Temporary employment.
15 The Commission shall establish polices on temporary employment for positions subject to
16 this Article, including the following:
17 (1) The implementation of the JoinNC Program under G.S. 126A-111 in a
18 consistent manner.
19 (2) Temporary employment.
20 "§ 126A-111. Use of JoinNC Program.
21 (a) All Cabinet agencies that utilize temporary employees shall employ them through the
22 JoinNC Program administered by OSHR, except as provided in subsection (e) of this section.
23 (b) Council of State agencies, constituent institutions of The University of North
24 Carolina, local agencies, and consolidated agencies as defined in G.S. 153A-77(b) may use the
25 JoinNC Program in accordance with this section.
26 (c) Temporary employees shall not be employed for longer than 11 consecutive months,
27 unless an exception is granted under subsection (f) of this section. After 11 consecutive months
28 of employment, a temporary employee is eligible for reinstatement on the job assignment after
29 the employee is separated for at least 31 consecutive calendar days. It is the responsibility of
30 participating agencies to provide a separation request or notification of a 31-day separation to
31 OSHR before the temporary employee exceeds 11 consecutive months of employment, unless an
32 exception under subsection (f) of this section applies. Failure to provide a timely separation
33 request to OSHR may limit an agency's future access to temporary employees.
34 (d) OSHR may prohibit any agency or entity, except the North Carolina National Guard,
35 from acquiring new temporary employees if the agency or entity has an invoice owed to JoinNC
36 that is (i) more than 90 days overdue and (ii) exceeds two hundred thousand dollars ($200,000).
37 If an agency or entity is prohibited, the prohibition shall continue until all overdue invoices are
38 paid.
39 (e) Notwithstanding the requirement of subsection (a) of this section, Cabinet agencies
40 may employ temporary employees outside of the JoinNC Program in the following
41 circumstances:
42 (1) The temporary employees are performing work that is information
43 technology-related.
44 (2) The Department of Transportation, Ferry Division, is employing temporary
45 employees when there is an established need for peak-season hires or when
46 the work requires a specific skillset beyond the scope of a temporary
47 employee.
48 (3) The Director in his or her discretion creates an exception when all of the
49 following conditions are met:
50 a. The JoinNC Program cannot meet the agency's employment needs for
51 the temporary position's classification.
